General interval comment: The lithology is a clayey nannofossil chalk that varies in color from a light greenish grey (GLEY1 8/5GY) to greenish grey (GLEY 1 7/10GY). Within the slightly darker intervals are thin laminae of greyish green (GLEY1 5/5G) and very thin light grey (GLEY 1 7/N) beds. Bioturbation is moderate, although it does appear to be higher in the darker intervals.
